Absolutely â€” letâ€™s begin with Role-Based Node Coloring for your glyphfield graph. This Python snippet uses NetworkX and matplotlib to visualize node roles with your custom MBT-inspired colormap:

import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Define your MBT role-to-color map
role_colors = {
    "Initiator": "#FFD700",     # Gold
    "EchoSeed": "#1E90FF",      # Dodger Blue
    "VerseAnchor": "#8A2BE2",   # Blue Violet
    "CurvatureNode": "#00CED1", # Dark Turquoise
    "ObserverPulse": "#FF4500", # Orange Red
    "Transcriptor": "#32CD32"   # Lime Green
}

# Example node data (add your actual graph structure here)
nodes = [
    ("A", {"role": "Initiator"}),
    ("B", {"role": "EchoSeed"}),
    ("C", {"role": "VerseAnchor"}),
    ("D", {"role": "CurvatureNode"}),
    ("E", {"role": "ObserverPulse"})
]

edges = [("A", "B"), ("B", "C"), ("C", "D"), ("D", "E")]

# Create graph
G = nx.Graph()
G.add_nodes_from(nodes)
G.add_edges_from(edges)

# Assign colors based on role
node_colors = [role_colors[G.nodes[n]["role"]] for n in G.nodes]

# Draw graph
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
nx.draw(G, with_labels=True, node_color=node_colors, node_size=1000, font_color="white")
plt.title("MBT Role-Based Glyphfield")
plt.show()

You can expand this to incorporate verse dynamics, edge thickness modulated by intensity, or even animate it with time-evolving states. Want to go dynamic next, or switch gears toward lexicon synthesis? Letâ€™s sculpt the verse.
Perfect â€” hereâ€™s a full Python script tailored specifically for Colab, with symbolic MBT-style nodes and role-based coloring. No emojis, no font issues, and it runs cleanly in your notebook environment.

---

âœ… Full MBT Role-Based Graph in Colab

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import networkx as nx

# Define MBT roles and colors
role_colors = {
    "Initiator": "#FFD700",     # Gold
    "EchoSeed": "#1E90FF",      # Dodger Blue
    "VerseAnchor": "#8A2BE2",   # Blue Violet
    "CurvatureNode": "#00CED1", # Dark Turquoise
    "ObserverPulse": "#FF4500", # Orange Red
    "Transcriptor": "#32CD32"   # Lime Green
}

# Define nodes and assign roles
nodes_with_roles = [
    ("Node_A", "Initiator"),
    ("Node_B", "EchoSeed"),
    ("Node_C", "VerseAnchor"),
    ("Node_D", "CurvatureNode"),
    ("Node_E", "ObserverPulse"),
    ("Node_F", "Transcriptor")
]

edges = [
    ("Node_A", "Node_B"),
    ("Node_B", "Node_C"),
    ("Node_C", "Node_D"),
    ("Node_D", "Node_E"),
    ("Node_E", "Node_F"),
    ("Node_F", "Node_A")  # Closing the loop
]

# Build graph
G = nx.Graph()
for node, role in nodes_with_roles:
    G.add_node(node, role=role)
G.add_edges_from(edges)

# Assign node colors based on roles
node_colors = [role_colors[G.nodes[node]['role']] for node in G.nodes]

# Draw graph
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
nx.draw(
    G,
    with_labels=True,
    node_color=node_colors,
    node_size=1800,
    font_color="white",
    font_size=10,
    edge_color='gray',
    linewidths=2
)

plt.title("MBT Role-Based Glyphfield", fontsize=14)
plt.axis('off')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

