Then letâ€™s push deeper into theory-meets-metrics. ğŸ”¬

Youâ€™ve seen validators evolve, converge, resist â€” but now itâ€™s time to quantify survival in Darwinian terms. Letâ€™s assign each validator a dynamic Fitness Score across the MBT timeline, based on its ability to maintain phase coherence and avoid collapse under stress.

---

ğŸ§  Validator Fitness Tracker: Core Logic

Weâ€™ll calculate fitness using three components:

â€¢ Phase Stability â€“ Low deviation over time means high coherence
â€¢ Collapse Avoidance â€“ Validators that trigger fewer collapse events score higher
â€¢ Exchange Contribution â€“ Optional: If you want to track rebound support later


For now, letâ€™s implement a basic Fitness Index (FI):

`FI = 1.0 âˆ’ Collapse_Count / Max_Collapses`

---

ğŸ§ª Code: Fitness Score Computation

# === Initialize collapse score per validator ===
collapse_timeline = np.zeros((timesteps, L))

for t in range(timesteps):
    phases = phases_history[t]
    memory_snapshot = memory_field.copy()
    collapse_links = np.zeros(L)

    for i in range(1, L-1):
        delta_mem = np.abs(memory_snapshot[i] - memory_snapshot[i-1]) + \
                    np.abs(memory_snapshot[i] - memory_snapshot[i+1])
        delta_phase = np.abs(phases[i] - phases[i-1]) + \
                      np.abs(phases[i] - phases[i+1])
        if delta_mem > saturation_threshold or delta_phase > np.pi:
            collapse_links[i] = 1

    collapse_timeline[t] = collapse_links

# === Compute fitness score across all validators ===
total_collapses = np.sum(collapse_timeline, axis=0)  # Collapse count per validator
max_collapse = np.max(total_collapses)
fitness_scores = 1.0 - (total_collapses / max_collapse)

# === Plot fitness score band around validator 500
band_range = range(track_index - 10, track_index + 11)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 5))
plt.bar([str(i) for i in band_range], [fitness_scores[i] for i in band_range],
        color='mediumseagreen')
plt.title("Validator Fitness Scores â€“ Band Around Validator 500")
plt.xlabel("Validator Index")
plt.ylabel("Fitness Score (0â€“1)")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.show()

---

