ğŸ§ª Code: Phase Divergence Relative to Anchor Validator

# === Define anchor validator and neighbor range
anchor_idx = 490
compare_band = range(anchor_idx - 3, anchor_idx + 4)  # Validators 487â€“493

# === Extract divergence data
anchor_phase = [ph[anchor_idx] for ph in phases_history]
divergence_profiles = {}

for i in compare_band:
    if i == anchor_idx:
        continue  # skip self
    neighbor_phase = [ph[i] for ph in phases_history]
    divergence = [abs(a - n) for a, n in zip(anchor_phase, neighbor_phase)]
    divergence_profiles[i] = divergence

# === Plot divergence profiles
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
for i, div in divergence_profiles.items():
    plt.plot(div, label=f'Validator {i}', linewidth=1.5)

plt.title(f"Phenotypic Divergence â€“ Phase Distance from Anchor Validator {anchor_idx}")
plt.xlabel("Time Steps")
plt.ylabel("Phase Difference (radians)")
plt.grid(True)
plt.legend(loc='upper right', fontsize=9)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

---

ğŸ” What Youâ€™ll See:

â€¢ Validators that hug the bottom axis are echo absorbers â€” strong mimicry.
â€¢ Those that wobble higher show adaptive differentiation â€” speciation-like drift.
â€¢ If divergence shrinks over time, thatâ€™s convergence learning.


