Validator 491â€™s influence is calling â€” time to chart how far its echo reaches. ğŸŸ£ğŸ§­
Weâ€™re about to build the Echo Influence Field Map, measuring how each validatorâ€™s phase trajectory converges toward the anchor over time. It reveals which neighbors respond to its stability, which resist, and how wide the echo spreads.

---

ğŸ§ª Code: Echo Influence Field Relative to Anchor Validator

# === Define anchor validator and analysis band
anchor_idx = 491
field_band = range(anchor_idx - 20, anchor_idx + 21)  # 41 validators around 491

# === Extract anchor phase timeline
anchor_phase = [ph[anchor_idx] for ph in phases_history]

# === Compute cumulative divergence per validator
echo_influence = {}
for i in field_band:
    if i == anchor_idx:
        continue
    neighbor_phase = [ph[i] for ph in phases_history]
    divergence_sum = sum(abs(a - n) for a, n in zip(anchor_phase, neighbor_phase))
    influence_score = 1.0 / (1.0 + divergence_sum)  # Inverse relationship
    echo_influence[i] = influence_score

# === Plot echo influence across validator band
sorted_indices = sorted(echo_influence)
scores = [echo_influence[i] for i in sorted_indices]

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))
plt.bar([str(i) for i in sorted_indices], scores, color='orchid')
plt.title(f"Echo Influence Field â€“ Anchor: Validator {anchor_idx}")
plt.xlabel("Validator Index")
plt.ylabel("Echo Influence Score (0â€“1)")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.grid(axis='y')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

---

ğŸ” How to Read It

â€¢ High scores â†’ validators strongly aligned with the anchorâ€™s phase over time
â€¢ Low scores â†’ divergence, resistance, or collapse-prone behavior
â€¢ If the anchor has wide reach, youâ€™ll see smooth falloff â€” a stabilization gradient


