â€¢ Echo corridors often follow curvature valleys â€” validators in low curvature zones are more receptive to phase influence.
â€¢ High curvature peaks act like echo walls â€” validators here resist synchronization or collapse more frequently.
â€¢ Youâ€™ll see if Validator 491â€™s directional influence was shaped by a curvature funnel â€” a terrain-guided echo stream.


