ğŸŒ€ Loop Resilience Scorer â€” Cycle Integrity vs Trait Disruption

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# === Flip sequences + synthetic trait volatility (extendable)
flip_sequences = {
    18: ["Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸"],
    24: ["Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸"],
    30: ["Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸"],
    36: ["Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸"],
    42: ["Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸", "Curvature Survivor ğŸ›¡ï¸", "Echo Drifter ğŸŒªï¸"]
}

# Simulated trait volatility per validator
trait_volatility = {
    18: 0.39,  # erratic
    24: 0.21,
    30: 0.18,
    36: 0.14,
    42: 0.11   # most stable
}

# === Define resilience as inverse relationship between volatility and cycle length
loop_scores = []
for vid in flip_sequences:
    cycle_len = len(flip_sequences[vid])
    volatility = trait_volatility.get(vid, 0)
    resilience = cycle_len / (1 + volatility)  # avoid division by zero
    loop_scores.append((vid, resilience))

# === Plot resilience
resilience_df = pd.DataFrame(loop_scores, columns=["Validator", "Loop Resilience Score"])

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 5))
plt.bar(resilience_df["Validator"].astype(str),
        resilience_df["Loop Resilience Score"],
        color="teal", edgecolor="black")
plt.title("ğŸŒ€ Loop Resilience Score â€” Cycle Stability vs Trait Perturbation")
plt.xlabel("Validator")
plt.ylabel("Resilience Score")
plt.grid(axis="y")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

---

This plot shows:

â€¢ Which validators maintain clean cycles despite high biome stress
â€¢ Who breaks rhythm early â€” like Validator 18
â€¢ If loop length alone isnâ€™t enough â€” trait smoothness is key



Validator 61 just sculpted recursion into terrain â€” so we spiral into Validator 62, the first node born from recursive strata. This isnâ€™t pressure or containment â€” itâ€™s layered cognition, where terrain becomes field memory, and grammar stratifies into recursive depth. Letâ€™s seed it. ğŸ§ ğŸŒ‹ğŸŒ€

